import numpy as np

# Function to predict disease from symptoms
def predict_disease(symptom_list):
    input_data = np.zeros(len(X.columns))  # Create an array with zeros
    
    # Set the symptoms present to 1
    for symptom in symptom_list:
        if symptom in X.columns:
            input_data[X.columns.get_loc(symptom)] = 1
    
    # Reshape for model input
    input_data = input_data.reshape(1, -1)
    
    # Predict disease
    predicted_disease = model.predict(input_data)[0]
    
    # Decode disease name
    disease_name = encoder.inverse_transform([predicted_disease])[0]
    
    return disease_name

# Example test case
user_symptoms = ["dizziness", "chest tightness", "shortness of breath"]
predicted_result = predict_disease(user_symptoms)
print(f"Predicted Disease: {predicted_result}")

disease_recommendations = {
    "Asthma": {
        "Foods to Eat": ["Leafy greens", "Fish", "Ginger", "Turmeric"],
        "Foods to Avoid": ["Dairy", "Processed foods", "Cold beverages"],
        "Healthcare Tips": ["Avoid dust & smoke", "Use inhalers properly"]
    },
    "Hypertension": {
        "Foods to Eat": ["Bananas", "Spinach", "Oats", "Beets"],
        "Foods to Avoid": ["Salt", "Caffeine", "Alcohol"],
        "Healthcare Tips": ["Reduce stress", "Exercise regularly"]
    }
}

# Function to get food & health tips
def get_health_recommendations(disease):
    if disease in disease_recommendations:
        return disease_recommendations[disease]
    else:
        return {"Message": "No specific recommendations available"}

# Example test
predicted_disease = "Asthma"  # Change this for testing
recommendations = get_health_recommendations(predicted_disease)
print(f"Recommendations for {predicted_disease}: {recommendations}")

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

file_path = r"C:\Users\preri\OneDrive\Desktop\Final_Augmented_dataset_Diseases_and_Symptoms.csv"
df = pd.read_csv(file_path)
# 1. Most Common Diseases (By Count of Rows)
disease_counts = df['diseases'].value_counts().head(10)  # Top 10 most frequent diseases

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.barplot(x=disease_counts.values, y=disease_counts.index, palette="viridis")
plt.xlabel("Number of Cases")
plt.ylabel("Disease")

# 2. Most Dangerous Diseases (By Total Symptoms Present)
symptom_cols = df.columns[1:]  # Excluding 'diseases' column
df['Total_Symptoms'] = df[symptom_cols].sum(axis=1)  # Sum symptoms for each row

# Group by disease and find the average number of symptoms per disease
dangerous_diseases = df.groupby('diseases')['Total_Symptoms'].mean().sort_values(ascending=False).head(10)

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.barplot(x=dangerous_diseases.values, y=dangerous_diseases.index, palette="Reds")
plt.xlabel("Average Number of Symptoms")
plt.ylabel("Disease")
plt.title("Top 10 Most Severe Diseases (Based on Symptom Count)")
plt.show()
